cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.SI 

This paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category as it introduces a new class of activation functions for neural networks. It may also be relevant to the neural networks (cs.NE), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and social and information networks (cs.SI) sub-categories as it discusses the performance of the proposed Goldilocks networks on image classification tasks and the tractability of data deformation through the layers.
